cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about named entity recognition (NER) for Vietnamese language using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (Bi-LSTM) and word embeddings, which are common techniques in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the performance of Vietnamese NER, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Networks and Communications). Finally, the paper mentions an evaluation campaign, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
